Key Match Events: Shadab Khan scored 52 with four sixes in 22 balls
Temba Bavuma and Aiden Markram were dismissed two balls apart in the last over
South Africa fell short by 33 runs
Pre-Game Insights: Pakistan's captain Babar Azam said they gave 100% in the last two matches and hoped for the best
South Africa captain Temba Bavuma demanded an improvement in batting and fielding
Post-Match Reflections: Babar Azam praised the team's performance, especially the efforts of Haris, Shadab, and Ifthikhar
Temba Bavuma expressed disappointment with the team's batting and fielding performance
Miscellaneous Highlights: Mohammed Haris played a 11-ball stay worth 28 runs
Rain delayed the game after Shadab's over
